"feed forward" is a very old idea.  A new audio amp using it as a feature is a bit odd.  Everything old is new again I guess.
It is a bit surprising that neither of the chip makers made 3 threads per core available.  Even if it costs a bit on single threaded performance, on a very multi-threaded work load it speeds things up.  You could avoid a lot of OS overhead in task switching by having the processor able to do more of them if there is a "stall" due to cache miss etc.
Â I am typing this on a machine with only 2 cores.  I think I am due for an upgrade.  
The wife's computer is even more due for upgrade.
